Firstly I think before I launch into what I'm doing on the 29th July I think I should give a brief explanation as to how I arrived at doing what I'll be doing on that day.

I'm a under grad currently studying Bio-Archaeology and on placement with Clwyd-Powys Archaeological Trust in Wales until Christmas, normally doing things like updating the records and using GIS.

Friday 29th I'll be joining my placement supervisor as we head to Wrexham to set up the Trust's stand at what I hear is THE event in Wales, The National Eisteddfod of Wales, which this year is in Wrexham and starts on the 30th July. We'll be taking most the leaflets and a small amount of the equipment needed over the week long event and setting it all up ready for the mayhem to begin on Saturday.

So it's not I'm afraid a very exciting day just travelling and laying out leaflets, if anything does happen or plans change I'll put up another post but for now that's about it.

