The first piece involving the Star Carr team was a shoot with Ben Elliott describing how his antler working experiments have helped him learn about Mesolithic technology and people's relationships with <a title="Arkive info about red deer" href="http://www.arkive.org/red-deer/cervus-elaphus/" target="_blank">red deer</a>.

[caption id="attachment_1131" align="alignleft" width="580"]<a href="http://www.dayofarchaeology.com/the-star-carr-project-gets-visitors/ben-explains-antler-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-1131"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1131" title="Ben explains antler working to Alice" alt="Ben explains antler working to Alice" src="http://www.dayofarchaeology.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Ben-explains-Antler-1-580x403.jpg" width="580" height="403" /></a> Ben, the project's expert, explains Mesolithic antler working to Alice.[/caption]

