Hello again from Mount Vernon!Â  My name is Laura and Iâm the Archaeology Laboratory Assistant and Volunteer Coordinator.Â  Work in the lab can vary greatly each day.Â  After spending some time this morning finding the perfect avatar for our Mount Vernon Day of Archaeology account (see below!), the assistant archaeologist and I spent some time reviewing distribution maps from the Phase II excavations of the George Washington Library site.Â  The distribution maps tell us where certain classes of artifacts were found and help us narrow down site locations.

