I spent this afternoon cross-mending ceramic sherds from an 18<sup>th</sup> century tin-glazed chamber pot, excavated from the neighboring Potomac Overlook site.Â  Â Cross-mending allows us to determine minimum vessel counts and helps us to understand the relationship between different layers of fill.

